original_comment_for_context:
Madam, you have aptly raised important issues in Parliament.

I would like to bring attention to the concerns regarding the reservation system. We pay taxes diligently, yet benefits seem to be extended to all, regardless of financial standing. 

Our children score 580 marks but are unable to secure paid seats, while others with scores as low as 400 manage to get admitted to professional colleges on free seats. It is becoming increasingly evident that individuals in more privileged financial positions are benefiting from this system. 

I strongly believe that reservation should be based on financial status, ensuring that support reaches those who genuinely need it. It would be greatly appreciated if this matter could be addressed.

It is becoming increasingly evident that individuals in more privileged financial positions are benefiting from this system. üö® Union Budget or Bihar Budget? üö®

This budget is not for the nation‚Äîit‚Äôs a state election campaign speech in disguise. Instead of addressing India‚Äôs economic concerns, the Finance Minister seems more focused on upcoming elections. 

What Bihar got?
Makhaana Board ‚úÖ

Patna airportimprovisation ‚úÖ
3 Center of excellence (500 cr) ‚úÖ
Additional 5 IITs and 5,000 new seats ‚úÖ

What has Karnataka lost? üëá
Karnataka‚Äôs rightful ask  as per the 15th Finance Commission Recommendations, 
‚Çπ5,495 Cr Special Grant‚ùå
‚Çπ6,000 Cr State-Specific Grant ‚ùå
‚Çπ1,300 Cr for Urban Local Bodies ‚ùå
‚Çπ826 Cr Health Grants ‚ùå
‚Çπ2,461 Cr MSP Dues ‚ùå

Meanwhile, the union budget in 2024 was a Andhra gets a budget, this year its a Bihar budget, UP in 2026, Gujarat in 2027‚Ä¶ Every year, the Union Budget looks more like a state budget for election-bound regions.

original_comment_for_context:
Raj ghat....
Raj Ghat is a memorial complex in Delhi, India. The first memorial was dedicated to Mahatma Gandhi where a black marble platform was raised to mark the spot of his cremation on 31 January 1948 and consists of an eternal flame at one end. Located on Delhi's Ring Road, a stone footpath leads to the walled enclosure that houses the memorial. Later the memorial complex was expanded to include memorials for other prominent Indian leaders including Charan Singh, Jawaharlal Nehru, Lal Bahadur Shastri, Indira Gandhi, Rajiv Gandhi, Chandra Shekhar and Atal Bihari Vajpayee.
